In a mixing bowl, beat butter and sugars. Add egg and vanilla mix well. Stir in pineapple and almonds. Combine dry ingredients; add to butter mixture. spread evenly into a foil-lined 8-in. x 4-in. x 2-in. loaf pan. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Invert dough onto a cutting board; remove foil. Cut into 1/4-in. slices; place on greased baking sheets. Bake at 350 degrees F for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on wire racks.